    To run your project from the terminal of this IDE, you can use the following single command:

    powershell
    npm --prefix ui run dev
    What this command does:
    --prefix ui: Tells npm to look for the package.json file inside the ui directory.
    run dev: Starts the Vite development server, which hosts your "IntelliPlan AI" premium interface.
    Important Notes:
    Dependencies: If this is your first time running it or if you've added new features, you may need to install dependencies first by running:
    powershell
    npm --prefix ui install
    Environment Variables: Ensure your .env file in the ui directory is correctly configured with your Jira and LLM settings, as the frontend relies on these for the premium features (like the proxy to Atlassian) to work correctly.
    Python Backend: Currently, your project logic is primarily handled in the React frontend (ui/src/App.jsx). The Python scripts in the tools/ folder are available for standalone processing or future backend integration.